  "Question": "<p>Let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_546\"><math alttext=\"a\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>a</mi></semantics></math></span> be a real number . The positive part of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_547\"><math alttext=\"a\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>a</mi></semantics></math></span>, denoted by <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_548\"><math alttext=\"a^{+}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></semantics></math></span> is given by expression <span class=\"math-container\">$$a^+ = \\text{if } a\\geq 0 \\text{ then <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_550\"><math alttext=\"a\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>a</mi></semantics></math></span> else } 0$$</span> The negative part of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_550\"><math alttext=\"a\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>a</mi></semantics></math></span>, denoted by <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_551\"><math alttext=\"a^{-}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></semantics></math></span> is given by expression <span class=\"math-container\">$$a^- = \\text{if } a\\geq 0 \\text{ then $0$ else } -a$$</span> Both <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_553\"><math alttext=\"a^{+}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></semantics></math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_554\"><math alttext=\"a^{-}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></semantics></math></span>  are non negative and the following relationship hold <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_555\"><math alttext=\"a=a^{+}-a^{-}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> Above is the text from my compiler optimization book and I cannot understand the relationship explained. How can <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_556\"><math alttext=\"a\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>a</mi></semantics></math></span> be a real number and have positive and negative parts?</p>",
